package.name: Solar
package.summary: Simple object library and application repository for PHP.
package.description:
Solar is a class library and application component suite for PHP 5 (and is PHP5 E_STRICT compliant). Solar provides simple, easy-to-comprehend classes and components for the common aspects of web-based rapid application development.
Solar is designed for developers who intend to distribute their applications to the whole world. This means, for example, the database driver functions work exactly the same way for each supported database. It also means that localization support is built in from the start.
Please visit http://solarphp.com/ for more information.
package.notes:
* SCHEMA CHANGE
* The Solar_Model_Nodes class, and the related 'nodes' table, have a schema change. The column 'part_of' has been renamed to 'parent_id', and the columns 'rank' has been renamed to 'position'. Please run the "docs/migrate/0.14.0-0.15.0/content.sql" script to update your database and eliminate PHP errors related to not being able to find these columns.
* Added new classes
* Added Solar_Uri_Action action URI manipulation (vice using Solar_Uri itself). Be sure to change the old $config['Solar_Uri']['action'] keys to $config['Solar_Uri_Action']['path'].
* Removed classes
* Solar_Model_Comments; to be replaced with a Solar_Content object
* Solar
* Solar::start() no longer silences session_start(), per talks with Jeff Surgeson
* Solar_App
* per idea from Jeff Surgeson, the App.php class provides the initial stylesheet value, instead of prefixing it in the layout script
* Solar_App_Bookmarks
* add.action.php properly adds the editor_handle now
* add.action.php now redirects to edit, instead of forwarding
* moved most inline styling to a CSS file
* Solar/App/Public/styles/default.css
* changed h2 and h3 font sizes (thanks Jeff Surgeson)
* Solar_Cache
* method life() renamed to getLife() to match coding standards
* method active() renamed to isActive() to match coding standards
* Solar_Controller_Page
* Modified _redirect() method so that it attempts to build the location properly for a page-and-action specification
* Solar_Filter
* formatDate(), formatTime(), and formatTimestamp() now accept integers as Unix timestamps (won't use strtotime() when the value is an integer now).
* Turned off error suppression in all methods
* For consistency, renamed blanks() and stripBlanks() to blank() and stripBlank() ... all character methods are singular.
* For consistency, renamed words() and stripWords() to word() and stripWord() ... all character methods are singular.
* The cast() method now uses settype() internally.
* The multiple() method now throws an exception if it can't execute one of the requested filters.
* Solar_Form
* The values() method now takes an optional argument to say which top-level element value you want to retrieve
* Solar/Locale
* added pt_BR translation (thanks Marcelo Araujo)
* added ACTION_* keys
* Solar_PathStack
* renamed findInclude() to find()
* Solar_Sql
* Now uses select('string') instead of select('statement') to return the SQL command as a string
* The select('statement') method now returns a PDOStatement object.
* Solar_Sql_Result
* Now implements Iterator, per suggestion from Travis Swicegood many moons ago.
* Solar_Sql_Select
* Added __toString() method
* Removed cols() method, use from() or one of the join() methods to select columns
* The from() and fetch() methods are now smarter about tracking tables internally
* Streamlined the fetch() column deconfliction logic
* The _tblCols() method now tracks all tables, not just tables with columns
* Solar_Sql_Table
* Added fetch() and fetchAll() methods
* renamed paging() to setPaging()
* Solar_Test_Assert
* Assertion methods now return bool to say if the assertion succeeded or failed
* Solar_Uri
* MAJOR BC BREAK: refactored to smaller method set; there are now only 5 methods (vice 16) ...
* __construct() works just the same as before, but no more 'action' and 'public' config keys; these are combined into a single 'path' key that indicates a path prefix. Used particularly in the Solar_Uri_Action and Solar_Uri_Public subclasses.
* set() takes the place of import(), importAction(), and importPublic()
* fetch() takes the place of export(), exportAction(), and exportPublic()
* quick() takes the place of toAction(), toPublic()
* setPath() takes the place of setInfoString()
* setQuery() takes the place of setQueryString()
* No more specialty methods for manipulating query elements, just use the public $query property (array)
* No more specialty methods for manipulating path-info elements; path-info is combined back into the $path property (array).
* The fetch() method returns only path?query#fragment ... if you need the scheme://user:pass@host/path?query#fragment, use fetch(true)
* Solar_Uri_Action takes the place of the old action-specific methods
* Solar_Uri_Public takes the place of the old public-specific methods
* Solar_User_Auth
* Now calls session_regenerate_id() on authentication status changes (and deletes previous session as well)
* The start() method no longer silences session_start(), per talks with Jeff Surgeson
* Solar_Valid
* Bugfix: the callback() method now properly uses ""$this"" instead of "self::"
